===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|en-au-have eyes bigger than one's stomach.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|have<has,,had> eyes bigger than one's stomach}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To [[take]] more [[food]] on one's plate than one can eat; to be [[greedy]].
#: ''He has '''eyes bigger than his stomach'''.''
#: ''You have '''eyes bigger than your stomach'''.''
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To want more than one can handle.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Bookkeeping For Dummies|page=75|books.google.com/books?isbn=1742469973|author=Veechi Curtis, Lynley Averis|year=2010|passage=When choosing software, don't '''have eyes bigger than your stomach'''. Rather, stick to whatever level of software you need, and no more.}}

